{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Blast Course is a first-person puzzle-platformer centered around the classic game mechanic of <strong>Rocket Jumping</strong>. Control Kit in a day at work testing &quot;Hyperboom&quot;, a revolutionary transport technology based on explosives. Overcome four different levels with the help of your own &quot;Hyperboom&quot; and its set of modifications while testing the viability of this new product.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">REVISITING A POPULAR AND CLASSIC MECHANIC</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">This game is, in a way, intended as a love letter to kinesthetic gameplay, exemplified through the possibility of combining complex movements with just one singular tool, bringing rocket jumping to the spotlight. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">MAKING ROCKET JUMPING UNDERSTANDABLE AND ACCESSIBLE</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">The goal of this game is to design rocket jumping from the ground up, bringing home its most engaging aspects, whilst streamlining it for a modern audience by getting rid of unnecessary complexities and making it more intuitive and less fiddly. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">KINESTHETIC PUZZLE LEVEL DESIGN: TECHNIQUE RATHER THAN SPEED</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">By conceiving complex jumps and maneuvers not as a test of skill, but as a solution to a puzzle, we can create levels that are potentially more complex, with more flexible pacing, and that put less pressure on players.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Project made for the B.A. in Interactive Product Design, B.F.A in Animation and B.F.A in Digital Design degrees of U-Tad, University of Technology, Arts and Design.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2655220/extras/U-TAD-orlarus.png?t=1733230086\" /></p>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"